cs.MOBILE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on developing a transportation mode detection system using mobile phones, which falls under the category of mobile computing. Therefore, cs.MOBILE is the most likely sub-category. The paper also leverages the phone serving cell information, which is related to network infrastructure and wireless communication, indicating that cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) is also a likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel feature extraction method to achieve high detection accuracy, which involves machine learning techniques, suggesting that cs.AI (artificial intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also presents an evaluation of the proposed system, which involves performance analysis and metrics, indicating that cs.SY (systems and control) is a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of logarithmic and linear RSS scales, which is related to data analysis and statistics, suggesting that cs.LG (machine learning) is also a possible sub-category.
